Subject: Re: [T2] Flux Core Welding Problems

On Tue, 31 Jul 2007, Jason Meyer wrote:

> I have a big piece of what I believe is galvanized metal that used to sit
> under my washer and drier. Can galvanized metal be welded to regular steel?
> If not, what resources would y'all suggest for getting pieces of steel to
> use for light body work and welding practice?

It can be welded, but it gives off nasty (as in poisonous) gases when you
do it.  Better to avoid welding it and get some mild steel to practice on.
